content: I don't see see any option to clearly disposition that the voter has already voted - some other thread suggested to choose  "Early Vote In Person"  - but will that prevent the voter from getting more calls from us?
~~That should do it.~~ For the record, see the below answers.

<@1199961707104190546> the campaign pulls voter records nightly and updates the lists accordingly, so if someone voted, they should fall of our lists within a couple of days of their vote being recorded as received

In the zPB we ask who the voter supported - and add that answer ex. "Strong Harris" and than thank the caller and end call. Eventually they get dropped from the lists when they actually vote (incase they were just saying that)
